[[File:Fuel pool.jpg|thumb|Spent nuclear fuel storage pool, similar to those at the Clab]] The '''Clab''', also known as ''Centralt mellanlager för använt kärnbränsle'' ([[swedish language|Swedish]] for 'Central holding storage for spent nuclear fuel') is an interim [[radioactive waste]] repository located about 25 kilometers north of [[Oskarshamn Nuclear Power Plant]] <ref name="SKB">{{cite web |url=http://www.skb.com/our-operations/clab/ |title=Clab – Central Interim Storage Facility for Spent Nuclear Fuel |publisher=SKB-Swedish Nuclear Fuel and Waste Management Company |website=skb.com |access-date=September 17, 2017}}</ref> and is owned by [[OKG AB|Oskarshamnsverkets Kraftgrupp AB]] (OKG), in [[Oskarshamn]]. It was opened in 1985 for the storage of spent [[nuclear fuel]] from all [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[nuclear power plant]]s. The fuel is stored for 30 to 40 years, in preparation for final storage.
The facility currently contains approximately 6,500 tons of [[high-level waste]], submerged in 8 meters of water, in pools 30 meters below the surface.<ref name="SKB"></ref> Contaminated reactor components, such as [[control rod]]s, are also stored at the facility.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stralsakerhetsmyndigheten.se/In-English/About-the-Swedish-Radiation-Safety-Authority1/Our-work-to-enhance-safety-/Facilities-in-Sweden/Clab-/ |title=Clab |publisher=Swedish Radiation Safety Authority |access-date=September 17, 2017}}</ref> Waste produced from Sweden's nuclear power plants will continue be stored at the facility until the [[Swedish Nuclear Fuel and Waste Management Company]] can complete construction of a more permanent storage site at [[Forsmark]].
==External links== *[https://web.archive.org/web/20101003083022/http://www.skb.se/templates/standard____15094.aspx Clab] Svensk Kärnbränslehantering AB about Clab (in Swedish)
