==Memory forensics== {{main|memory forensics}} Memory forensics tools are used to acquire and/or analyze a computer's volatile memory (RAM). They are often used in incident response situations to preserve evidence in memory that would be lost when a system is shutdown, and to quickly detect stealthy malware by directly examining the operating system and other running software in memory. {| class="wikitable sortable" border="1" |- ! scope="col" | Name ! scope="col" | Vendor/Sponsor ! scope="col" | [[Computing platform|Platform]] ! scope="col" | License <!-- Please only include tools that either a) have a stable, sourced Wikipedia article OR b) are cited from a reliable, independent (i.e. not the company website) source --> |- | [[Belkasoft Evidence Center]] || Belkasoft || Windows || proprietary |- | [[Belkasoft Live RAM Capturer]] || Belkasoft || Windows || Free |- | [[Volatility (memory forensics)|Volatililty]] || Volatile Systems || Windows & Linux || Free (GPL) |- | [[WindowsSCOPE]] || BlueRISC || Windows || proprietary |}
==Mobile device forensics== {{main|mobile device forensics}} Mobile forensics tools tend to consist of both a hardware and software component. Mobile phones come with a diverse range of connectors, the hardware devices support a number of different cables and perform the same role as a write blocker in computer devices. {| class="wikitable sortable" border="1" |- ! scope="col" | Name ! scope="col" | [[Computing platform|Platform]] ! scope="col" | License ! scope="col" | Version ! scope="col" class="unsortable" | Description |- | [[Belkasoft Evidence Center]] || Windows || proprietary || || Software product which supports mobile and computer forensics |- | [[.XRY|MicroSystemation XRY/XACT]]<ref name="mf" /> || Windows || proprietary || || Hardware/Software package, specializes in deleted data |}
==Software forensics== {{main|software forensics}} Software forensics is the science of analyzing software source code or binary code to determine whether intellectual property infringement or theft occurred. It is the centerpiece of lawsuits, trials, and settlements when companies are in dispute over issues involving software patents, copyrights, and trade secrets. Software forensics tools can compare code to determine correlation, a measure that can be used to guide a software forensics expert.
