'''S-55''' was an American [[satellite]] launched by [[NASA]] on 30 June 1961 as part of the [[Explorers program]].<ref>{{cite web|title=S-55|url=http://www.astronautix.com/craft/s55.htm|publisher=[[Encyclopedia Astronautica]]|accessdate=2018-06-08}}</ref> Explorer (S-55), also known as Meteoroid Sat A, was launched using a [[Scout 5]] rocket from the [[Wallops Flight Facility]]. Its mission was to evaluate the launch vehicle, and investigate [[micrometeoroid]] impact and penetration. The mission failed because the third stage failed to ignite and the spacecraft did not achieve orbit.

